  "prompt": "How much does it cost to attend a TED talk?",
  "response": "The cost to attend a TED talk can vary significantly depending on the type of event. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **TED Conference**: Attending the main TED Conference can cost several thousand dollars, typically ranging from $5,000 to $10,000 or more for a badge, depending on the year and location. This fee usually includes access to talks, workshops, and various networking opportunities.\n\n2. **TEDx Events**: TEDx events are independently organized and can have lower ticket prices, often ranging from free to a few hundred dollars, depending on the venue and host organization.\n\n3. **TED Salon**: These are more intimate discussions and events and typically have a lower cost, though the pricing can vary.\n\n4. **Online Access**: Some events or talks may be available for free online via the TED website or their YouTube channel.\n\nIt's always a good idea to check the specific event's website for the most accurate and up-to-date information on ticket prices and availability.",
